<Content>Very Noisy! We had a three room suite right on the Zocalo, which initially looked quite nice, but it turned out to be the noisiest place we had ever stayed! There were people talking on bullhorns in the square until late every night and lots of traffic noises and alarms going off all night, including a car crash one night. There is a flag raising ceremony every morning at 5:45 a.m. (involving drums and bugles) which woke us up every time. Also, the lighting in our suite was very dim for reading at night. It was not a good place despite the fact that the lobby was very beautiful and the staff was nice and helpful. A bellman named Constantino spoke very good English and fixed us up with taxis, including a driver to go to the Pyramids, etc. 
