<Content>Be Prepared for LOTS of NOISE and NO SLEEP The good part: you are right on the Zocalo, with some rooms offering perfect views thereof. The shower was pretty decent too, and the rooms are nice sized. The hotel itself is beautiful, with blue tile, and a pretty decent restaurant on the roof that is reasonably priced.The bad part: There is an inner courtyard thing-- that means lots of noise that echoes through the hotel. The hotel runs tours that start at 6 or 7 AM. That means that families, and often kids aged 4-17 are running around the hotel screaming at 6 or 7 am. that's really loud and echoes. Lastly, every night on weekends, and some nights on weekdays, there are concerts, drums and other performances in or around the Zocolo. They're really loud. You won't sleep. At all. Unless you're deaf.We got a corporate rate and they hooked us up with a suite, but if we had paid full price, it would have been a total rip off. 
