<Content>No No "amarse"" On checking in we were shown to an inside room with twin beds. I smiled while encircling my wife's waist sayin NO! No! Amarse! The bell hop smiled, called the desk  we were soon in a room at the top of the hotel with a fantastic view of the Zocalo. Rooms a bit plain, but very clean. Had all the extras I need, hair dryer, wall safe, host bar at prices even I could afford ect. The one draw back was that we were right under the dance floor of the night club, but it closes very early so was not a real problem. We spent New Years eve first on the roof, than in our room watching the incredible action on the Zocalo. Our room had a balcony, but was very small with a low low railing. It was a straight drop of a 100' plus so we kept the doors open, bu did not venture on it. I see that another reviewer belayed the lack of dining in the area. We did not find this true. Our number one find was Cicero Centenario, a 5 star eatery in a old colonial mansion just a few blocks away. Several different groups of musicians strolled through the various dining rooms. The food  service could not be better. Our bill for a 5 course dinner (my wife had 3 glasses of vino) with tip was $38.00 US. Best value I have ever found in Mecico. We walked back to the Majestic, but best to call a cab. Anyways a good hotel with a great location  a Great Dining find at Cireros! 
