<Content>Great in the historic center! The Best Western Majestic, in the historic district in Mexico City, is a lovely old hotel and a good value. The lobby is beautifully restored and many rooms have been recently updated. My room overlooked the Zocalo, with the Metropolitan Cathedral to the left and the Government Palace across the plaza. Next to the Cathedral is the excavation of the Templo Mayor with its excellent museum.I had heard reports of noise but found the room relatively quiet, especially for a city hotel. Service was excellent. Good restaurants are nearby, including Sanborn's at the House of Tiles and Tacuba, a few blocks away. A metro station is located in the Zocalo and is very user friendly. 
