<Content>Wished it were better... The lobby and hallways of this hotel are truly gorgeous, which makes the very plain guest rooms something of a letdown. The staff are friendly and helpful. Rather than asking whether we would prefer a Zocalo or Courtyard view the desk clerk simplified the choice as Noisy or Quiet. I definitely recommend the rooftop restaurant, not for its competent food but for the amazing view of the zocalo and the cathedral. If it all becomes too much this is a great place to retreat to. Come admire the lobby, enjoy the view from the restaurant, but stay somewhere else where you can get a better value for your money. My review is admittedly colored by the following: It was quite warm during our visit, prompting us to leave our window open all night. I was awakened by a buzzing insect during the night and in the morning found both myself and my husband covered from literally head to toe in red bites that eventually became very itchy. We looked like we had smallpox. After changing hotels we had no more insect problems. 
