<Content>Best Western Majestic Hotel In August of 2002, my wife and I stayed at the Best Western Majestic Hotel. Overall, we were impressed with the building's appearance and the staff. The hotel is very well maintained and the lobby and restuarant were in fine shape. The staff could not have been more helpful or pleasant. However, the room did show its age somewhat. The room was clean and certainly did not want for anything, but the bathroom and the furniture probably date back to the beginnings of the hotel. We dined at the hotel's restuarant for both dinner and breakfast, and both meals were outstanding. I would reccommend eating there because the food is good, and the view of the Historic Center is unbeatable. The hotel's location is very convenient for exploring the this part of the city. During the day, there are a lot of places to see. However, at night, there are few places to eat or visit in the Historic Center, and I would recommend either staying in the hotel or taking a hotel taxi somewhere else. 
